---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Projects - Bradley Spillert">
  <section class="pt-32 pb-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="section-heading fade-in">Projects</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-500 mb-12 fade-in">
        Things I've built because I wanted them to exist.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-14">
        <div class="fade-in">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-4 mb-2">
            <h3 class="text-white text-lg font-medium">
              <a href="https://github.com/spillertb/flight-software" target="_blank" rel="noopener">flight-software</a>
            </h3>
            <a href="https://github.com/spillertb/flight-software" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-400 text-sm shrink-0">GitHub</a>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-2">
            Open source ground control station for ArduPilot drones. Web-based, built with React, TypeScript, and CesiumJS for 3D mapping. Packaged with Electron for desktop. This is what I'm spending most of my time on right now.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">React, TypeScript, CesiumJS, Electron, ArduPilot</p>
        </div>

        <div class="fade-in">
          <h3 class="text-white text-lg font-medium mb-2">Autonomous Quadcopter</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-2">
            7-inch quad running ArduPilot with ExpressLRS radio. Flies fully autonomous waypoint missions -- 5+ miles, no manual input. I built the airframe, tuned the PIDs, and set up the telemetry link.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">ArduPilot, ExpressLRS, FPV</p>
        </div>

        <div class="fade-in">
          <h3 class="text-white text-lg font-medium mb-2">MAVLink over ELRS</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-2">
            Technical writeup on running MAVLink telemetry over ExpressLRS. How to get reliable bidirectional telemetry on an RC link that was never designed for it.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">MAVLink, ExpressLRS, telemetry</p>
        </div>

        <div class="fade-in">
          <h3 class="text-white text-lg font-medium mb-2">CoreXY 3D Printer</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-2">
            Custom FDM printer built from scratch. Designed the frame and motion system in Fusion 360, runs Marlin firmware. Prints PLA, PETG, and TPU.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Fusion 360, Marlin, mechanical design</p>
        </div>

        <div class="fade-in">
          <h3 class="text-white text-lg font-medium mb-2">Gyro Glove</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-2">
            Senior capstone -- a wearable gesture controller for RC aircraft. Tilt your hand to fly the plane. Custom PCBs with an IMU, radio transceiver, and a lot of signal processing.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">PCB design, IMU, embedded C, wireless</p>
        </div>

        <div class="fade-in">
          <h3 class="text-white text-lg font-medium mb-2">Polar Plotter</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-[15px] leading-relaxed mb-2">
            Won Best Hardware Hack at HackUMass. A 2-motor polar coordinate plotter that draws anything you give it. Built in 36 hours on too much coffee.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Arduino, stepper motors, hackathon</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
